==English==
===Noun===
'''patent'''  (''plural:'' '''[[patents]]''') short form of [[Anglo-French]] ''lettre patent'' "open letter".
# A declaration issued by a [[government]] agency declaring someone the inventor of a new [[invention]] and having the privelege of stopping others from making, using or selling anything containing the patented invention (presumably unless they pay royalties).  Also '''letters patent'''.
# A specific grant of ownership of a piece of property.  Also '''land patent'''.
# Patent leather: A type of [[vinyl]] or [[plastic]], typically used for shoes.

===Adjective===
'''patent''' from [[Latin]] ''patens'' "open, lying open".

# In [[wikipedia:biology|biology]], to be open, unobstructed, or expanded.
# Something that is explicit and obvious, i.e. ''patently obvious''.

